ref refid="aff0010" id="crf0040"><ce:sup>a</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref><ce:cross-ref refid="cr0010" id="crf0050"><ce:sup>⁎</ce:sup></ce:cross-ref><ce:e-address type="email" xlink:href="mailto:victorlopez.pardo@usc.es" id="ea0040">victorlopez.pardo@usc.es</ce:e-address></ce:author><ce:affiliation id="aff0010" affiliation-id="S0370269325000188-0f8d2b6769bc088e9ed4c1453dc076f9"><ce:label>a</ce:label><ce:textfn>Instituto Galego de Física de Altas Enerxías IGFAE, Universidade de Santiago de Compostela, Santiago de Compostela, 15782, Galicia, Spain</ce:textfn><sa:affiliation><sa:organization>Instituto Galego de Física de Altas Enerxías IGFAE</sa:organization><sa:organization>Universidade de Santiago de Compostela</sa:organization><sa:city>Santiago de Compostela</sa:city><sa:state>Galicia</sa:state><sa:postal-code>15782</sa:postal-code><sa:country iso3166-1-alpha-3="ESP">Spain</sa:country></sa:affiliation><ce:source-text id="srct0005">Instituto Galego de Física de Altas Enerxías IGFAE, Universidade de Santiago de Compostela, Santiago de Compostela, 15782, Galicia, Spain</ce:source-text></ce:affiliation><ce:affiliation id="aff0020" affiliation-id="S0370269325000188-8ac218310a6ecb4a716717c52654daf3"><ce:label>b</ce:label><ce:textfn>Departament de Física Quàntica i Astrofísica and Institut de Ciències del Cosmos, Universitat de Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1, Barcelona, 08028, Catalonia, Spain</ce:textfn><sa:affiliation><sa:organization>Departament de Física Quàntica i Astrofísica</sa:organization><sa:organization>Institut de Ciències del Cosmos</sa:organization><sa:organization>Universitat de Barcelona</sa:organization><sa:address-line>Martí i Franquès 1</sa:address-line><sa:city>Barcelona</sa:city><sa:state>Catalonia</sa:state><sa:postal-code>08028</sa:postal-code><sa:country iso3166-1-alpha-3="ESP">Spain</sa:country></sa:affiliation><ce:source-text id="srct0010">Departament de Física Quàntica i Astrofísica and Institut de Ciències del Cosmos, Universitat de Barcelona, Martí i Franquès 1, Barcelona, 08028, Catalonia, Spain</ce:source-text></ce:affiliation><ce:correspondence id="cr0010"><ce:label>⁎</ce:label><ce:text>Corresponding author.</ce:text></ce:correspondence></ce:author-group><ce:date-received day="20" month="12" year="2024"/><ce:date-revised day="9" month="1" year="2025"/><ce:date-accepted day="10" month="1" year="2025"/><ce:miscellaneous id="ms0010">Editor: F. Gelis</ce:miscellaneous><ce:data-availability id="dav0001"><ce:section-title id="st0010">Data availability</ce:section-title><ce:para id="pr0040">No data was used for the research described in the article.</ce:para></ce:data-availability></simple-head><body><ce:sections><ce:para id="pr0010">During our investigations, we have found an error in our previous estimates. The error is purely numerical and not conceptual. It has to do with the translation of the units that our code uses to physical units. Thus, when using the Schrödinger equation to find the bound states, our error propagates to the solution, affecting both axes in the plots. We do find a substantially larger dissociation temperature. This is one of the main results of our study and, for this reason, we report here the corrected results.</ce:para><ce:para id="pr0020">The error affects the computation of the binding energy and the mean square radius. As such, <ce:cross-ref refid="fg0010" id="crf0060">Fig. 4</ce:cross-ref><ce:float-anchor refid="fg0010"/> and <ce:cross-ref refid="fg0020" id="crf0070">Fig. 5</ce:cross-ref><ce:float-anchor refid="fg0020"/> must substitute the corresponding figures in our article. The dissociation temperature is <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altimg="si1.svg"><mml:mi>T</mml:mi><mml:mo>∼</mml:mo><mml:mn>350</mml:mn><mml:mspace width="0.25em"/><mml:mrow><mml:mi mathvariant="normal">MeV</mml:mi></mml:mrow></mml:math>, which is 50% higher than the one we found before correcting the error. This does not change the qualitative result, that the <mml:math xmlns:mml="http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML" altimg="si2.svg"><mml:mi>X</mml:mi><mml:mo stretchy="false">(</mml:mo><mml:mn>3872</mml:mn><mml:mo stretchy="false">)</mml:mo></mml:math> would survive up to above the phase transition if it is a tetraquark state.</ce:para><ce:para id="pr0030">The rest of the results of our paper remain unchanged.</ce:para> </ce:sections><ce:conflict-of-interest id="coi0001"><ce:section-title id="st0020">Declaration of Competing Interest</ce:section-title><ce:para id="pr0050">The authors declare that they have no known competing financial interests or personal relationships that could have appeared to influence the work reported in this paper.</ce:para></ce:conflict-of-interest></body></simple-article>
